release.title: The Girl from Ipanema: The Bossa Nova Years

annotation.text:
track credits can be found in the LP version here: http://www.discogs.com/release/514128
matching 4cd version is here: http://www.discogs.com/release/2617137 (but described as EU release)

1-1 to 1-7 – recorded February 13th, 1962 by Ed Green In Washington D.C.
1-8 to 1-15 – recorded August 27-28 by George Kneurr and Frank Loca in N.Y.C. (see ''[http://musicbrainz.org/release-group/f58a0384-8e31-3645-85d8-7889cca2ad64|Big Band Bossa Nova]'')
2-1 to 2-11 – recorded February 8, 9 and 27, 1963 by Bob Simpson, Ray Hall and Phil Ramone in N.Y.C. (see ''[http://musicbrainz.org/release/c7026676-ce90-4e37-9300-3dad66c32585|Jazz Samba Encore!]'')
2-12 – "Tribute to Stan" (only found in cd version)
3-1 to 3-8 – recorded March 18-19, 1963 by Phil Ramone in N.Y.C. (see ''[http://musicbrainz.org/release/3dbe8250-a4e4-4bc4-a32c-db0e3a88375d|Getz/Gilberto]'')
3-9 to 4-7 – recorded March 21-22, 1963 by Bob Simpson in N.Y.C. (4-1 to 4-7, see ''[http://musicbrainz.org/release-group/1162f5d2-e4c6-38bd-a438-202f8fed0060|Stan Getz with guest artist Laurindo Almeida]'')
4-8 to 4-10 – recorded October 9, 1964 by Bob Simpson in N.Y.C. (previously unissued, performed at a Carnegie Hall concert)
